         <abstract>
            <p>Let V&lt;sub&gt;2n&lt;/sub&gt; be an H-matrix of order 2n constructible by using circulant n × n submatrices. A recursive method has been found to construct V&lt;sub&gt;4n&lt;/sub&gt; by using circulatn 2n × 2n submatrices which are derived from n × n submatrices of a given V&lt;sub&gt;2n&lt;/sub&gt;. A similar method can be applied to a given W&lt;sub&gt;4n&lt;/sub&gt;, an H-matrix of Williamson type with odd n, to construct W&lt;sub&gt;8m&lt;/sub&gt;. All V&lt;sub&gt;2n&lt;/sub&gt; consetructible by the standard type, for 1 ≥ n ≥ 16, and some V&lt;sub&gt;2n&lt;/sub&gt; for n ≥ 20, are listed and classified by this method.</p>
          </abstract>
